modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to block devices, including sector-aligned data transfers and device metadata retrieval. Operates on raw byte sequences and block device descriptors. Used to implement storage backends in networked applications requiring direct disk access.

Provides functions to interact with sector-addressible block devices, including reading and writing data in chunks of sectors, querying device information, and handling errors. Operates on types like `int64` for sector addresses, `Cstruct.t list` for buffer management, and custom error types for I/O failures. Used to manage persistent storage operations in networked or embedded systems, such as reading disk sectors or writing data to a storage device.
